Private constructor. Used internally to create a NumberOptionPane dialog.

Parameters:
parent - the parent component of the dialog, can be null; see showDialog for details
aTitle - Title of the dialog
aLabel1 - Text of the first inside label of the dialog
aLabel2 - Text of the second inside label of the dialog
df - DecimalFormat of the input value
defaultValue1 - first default displayed value when the dialog is displayed
defaultValue2 - second default displayed value when the dialog is displayed
min - Minimum allowed value for the input value
max - Maximum allowed value for the input value

Displays a GdpCurveChooser dialog, and returns a Number.

Parameters:
parent - the parent component of the dialog, can be null; see showDialog for details
title - Title of the dialog.
label - Text of the inside label of the dialog.
df - DecimalFormat of the input value.
min - Minimum allowed value for the input value.
max - Maximum allowed value for the input value.
defaultValue - Default displayed value when the dialog is displayed.
Returns:
A number if OK has been pressed, otherwise null.
